# Day 5 – Cloud Troubleshooting and Monitoring

## Objective
Learn how to identify and fix common issues in a cloud environment.

## Troubleshooting Scenarios

### Scenario 1 – Nginx Service Stopped
Stopped Nginx and observed that the website became inaccessible.

Command used:

sudo systemctl stop nginx

Fix:

sudo systemctl start nginx

### Scenario 2 – Backend Server Stopped
Stopped Python HTTP server and observed a 502 Bad Gateway error.

Fix:

python3 -m http.server 8000

## Logs Checked

Nginx logs:

sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log

System logs:

sudo journalctl -xe

## Monitoring Commands

top
free -h
df -h

## Key Learning

Troubleshooting requires checking services, logs, networking, and system resources systematically.
